##
##  WHAT THIS SCRIPT GENERATES
##  --------------------------
##  An Excel workbook (monthly_total_returns.xlsx) with one sheet
##  per ticker, plus a combined Summary sheet. Each sheet contains:
##
##    • Month         — last trading day of each month (YYYY-MM-DD)
##    • Close         — actual raw closing price on the last trading day
##    • Dividends     — total cash dividends paid during that month
##    • Total Return  — (Close_t + Dividends_t - Close_{t-1}) / Close_{t-1}
##                      true buy-and-hold monthly total return, including
##                      all dividends received during the month
##
##  The Summary sheet shows all tickers side-by-side for easy comparison.
##
##  TWO ADDITIONAL CHART SHEETS
##  ---------------------------
##  • Chart — Normalized Prices : All tickers rebased to 100 on month 1,
##    showing relative price appreciation over the period.
##  • Chart — Cumulative Return  : Cumulative total return index (starting
##    at 100), compounding monthly total returns (dividends included).
##    This is the true wealth-growth comparison.
##
##  NOTE ON MONTHLY AGGREGATION
##  ---------------------------
##  Data is downloaded daily then aggregated to month-end:
##    • Close     = last trading day's closing price of the month
##    • Dividends = sum of all daily dividends paid during the month
##  This correctly captures every dividend payment regardless of
##  ex-dividend timing within the month.
##
##  NOTE ON THE FIRST ROW
##  ---------------------
##  The first month has no prior closing price, so its Total Return
##  is left blank (N/A). All subsequent rows are complete.
##
## ============================================================
##  INSTRUCTIONS: Edit only the three parameters below.
##  Do not modify anything beneath the divider line.
## ============================================================

